  "prompt": "What if we put petrol in diesel engine or vice versa?",
  "response": "Putting the wrong type of fuel in an engine can cause serious damage:\n\nPetrol in a Diesel Engine:\n1. Petrol acts as a solvent, damaging diesel fuel pump\n2. Causes increased friction and potential engine seizure\n3. Can destroy fuel injectors\n4. Leads to complete engine failure\n5. Repair costs can be extremely high\n6. May require full engine replacement\n\nDiesel in a Petrol Engine:\n1. Diesel won't ignite properly in petrol engine\n2. Engine won't start or run\n3. Less severe damage compared to petrol in diesel\n4. Fuel system might need cleaning\n5. Lower risk of catastrophic engine damage\n\nPrevention:\n1. Always double-check fuel type\n2. Pay attention at fuel station\n3. Use fuel pump nozzle designed for specific fuel\n4. If misfueling occurs, do NOT start the engine\n5. Call a professional to drain the fuel system\n\nBest practice is to immediately stop and call for professional assistance if you realize you've put the wrong fuel in your vehicle.",
